    "C.2 Deep Q-learningDeep Q-learning identifies the optimal action-value function Q(s, a) from which the optimal policy is extracted.",
    "Q-Learning relies on the Bellman optimality criterion [666,667].",
    "By separating the reward r 0 at the first step, the recursion formula of the optimal state-value function, i.e., the Bellman optimality criterion, can be established: V (s) = maxHere, s represents the next state after s. This can be done analogously for the action-value function.Q(s, a) = max π E π r 0 + γ Q(s, a)(94)The recursion enables an update formula, referred to as temporal difference (TD) learning [668,669].",
